The paper proposes improvements to temporal convolutional networks for speech separation, which is a task related to speech processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound). The paper also involves deep learning techniques and optimization methods, which are related to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions permutation invariant training, which is a technique used in speech separation and source separation tasks, and is related to sub-category cs.SI (Signal Processing).
